thread.title: Millions of Myanmar citizens abroad miss chance to vote
thread.title_full: Millions of Myanmar citizens abroad miss chance to vote | News24

author: news24.com
title: Millions of Myanmar citizens abroad miss chance to vote
text:
Yangon - Most of the more than 2 million Myanmar citizens living abroad have failed to register for postal voting in the November polls, an official said on Wednesday.
Only about 18 000 of more than 2 million people registered as living abroad had sent in applications before the deadline, said Tin Aye, chairperson of the Union Election Commission.
"Without co-operation from them, what else we can do for them?" he said.
Myanmar has an estimated population of 51.5 million.
